    "In 1883 met Sir James Guthrie (1859-1920), and artist and later president of the Scottish Royal Academy.": [],
    "The following year Caw began his career as an art critic, striking up friendships with the Scottish art community, including Sir James Lawton Wingate (1846 - 1924), president of the Royal Scottish Academy, the artists Edward Arthur Walton (1860 - 1922), Alexander Roche (1863-1921), and William McTaggart (1835-1910), the latter the pioneer of Scottish impressionism.": [
